Claims CLAIMS: 1 . A method of managing bandwidth of a plurality of Multicast Adaptive Bitrate, MABR, data streams in an Internet Protocol Television, IPTV, over Data Over Cable Service Interface Specification, DOCSIS, system, wherein a bandwidth bottleneck exists on either an inbound, IP-network side of a Cable Modem Termination System, CMTS, (18) or on an outbound, DOCSIS/RF-network side of the CMTS, the method comprising: when the bottleneck is on the outbound, DOCSIS/RF-network side of the CMTS, configuring (3) multiple virtual pipes on the inbound, IP-network side, wherein one virtual pipe is configured for each service group to manage the bandwidth per service group for output RF ports on the CMTS; and when the bottleneck is on the inbound, IP-network side of the CMTS, configuring (4) one virtual pipe on the inbound, IP-network side to manage the bandwidth for input Ethernet ports on the CMTS. 2. The method according to claim 1 , wherein the method is performed by a MABR Bandwidth Control Agent, BCA, (16) and further comprises: receiving (151 ) the plurality of MABR data streams (15), each data stream comprising a plurality of data segments separated by gaps coincident with gaps in each of the other data streams, wherein each data stream includes data from a different multicast address and each data stream is encoded at a different bit rate; joining (152) a first one of the data streams; during one of the coincident gaps between data segments, leaving (153) the first one of the data streams and joining a different, second one of the data streams without video data loss; utilizing (154) a segment cache (26) to remove the gaps between the data segments in the second data stream; and transmitting (155) the second data stream to the CMTS at the bit rate of the second data stream and without any gaps. 3. The method according to claim 1 , wherein the method is performed by a MABR Bandwidth Control Agent, BCA, (16) and further comprises allocating bandwidth within a 