location includes: determining (65) whether the channel can upgrade to the bitrate of the next highest MABR bandwidth allocation; when the channel can upgrade to the bitrate of the next highest MABR bandwidth allocation, changing (67) the bitrate for the channel to the next highest bitrate and returning to the step of computing (61 ) the inadequacy metric; and when the channel cannot upgrade to the bitrate of the next highest MABR bandwidth allocation, taking no action (66). 9. The method according to claim 8, wherein once all bitrates are determined, for each channel in the sorted list of applied channels (68), the step of performing (72) an IGMP join to the determined channel multicast bitrate for the newly joined channel includes: determining (69) whether the channel is already connected to a correct IGMP group; when the channel is already connected to a correct IGMP group, skipping (71 ) the channel; and when the channel is not already connected to a correct IGMP group, performing (72) the IGMP join to the determined channel multicast bitrate for the newly joined channel. 10. The method according to claim 1 , wherein the method is performed by a MABR Bandwidth Control Agent, BCA, (83) and further comprises: receiving the plurality of MABR data streams (82), wherein each data stream is non-gapped and includes data from a different multicast address and each data stream is encoded at a different bit rate; 

